value: Voice is much louder compared to harms and band in A. Chorus a tiny bit better but bc of loudness in A. Sounds a bit muddy in B, one extreme to the other (this seemed better in the chorus).

A - bass is way too overpowering, has a lot of lowend but if had 1-2kHz it would cut through better, bass is overpowering guitars, not much seperation. Selected - snare instantly a lot thinner, but guitar and bass go together a lot more, like the top end on the kick, vocal has more topend which helps it cut through the mid heavy mix.
Clarity straight away better, every element is clearer, vocals more balanced.
More clarity across the board in selection.
A sounded muddy, B sounded slightly less muddy but still not perfect.
Selected - high end better with drums, a lot more balanced. Drums a little bit louder but the quality of sound is better, vocal comes through a little more.
Overall selected sounded clearer, but vocals needed to be louder.
A kick got completely lost with the bass, no high end with kick. B was much clearer on that front. Vocals in B didn't like EQ, sounded really scooped around the mids.
Opposite had vocals really loud. Second one had better drum/snare clarity.
